Prospectus

Asako Mikami

February 14, 2019

Pizza to the Polls is a 501(c)(4) nonprofit organization that delivers pizzas during elections to polling locations. Voters send tweets to @PizzaToThePolls, and then Pizza To The Polls responds back. A typical response states that pizzas have been requested to be delivered to a polling location followed by the address. On their homepage, Pizza to the Polls count 10,793 pizzas sent to 611 polling locations across 41 states during the 2018 midterm election.

In this project, I have scraped @PizzaToThePolls’s tweets containing polling locations to which pizzas were delivered in response to voters waiting in line. The result is presented in the map below.
